<main id="main" class="wrap">

  <section class="hero">
    <div class="crumbs">
      <a href="/elixir">jonnify</a>
      <span class="sep">/</span>
      <span class="here">Agile Agent Workflow</span>
    </div>
    <p class="eyebrow">Agile Agent Workflow &middot; course overview</p>
    <h1>The agile agent <span class="ex">workflow</span></h1>
    <p class="lede">Pragmatic Programming with Claude Agents &mdash; a way of building software in which a human supplies
      judgement, taste, and acceptance, and a Claude agent supplies fast, exact implementation. Paired over thin,
      provable increments, the two ship reliable systems neither would reach alone. The course opens with the framework
      you will build &mdash; two layers, four artifacts, one loop &mdash; then teaches each part in depth and proves it
      on one running project.</p>
    <p class="kicker">The practical project is the <strong>Portal</strong>: a learning platform carried from an empty
      repository to a deployed, multi-surface system &mdash; a branded store, an event-sourced engine behind one
      facade, a Phoenix web application, a Telegram bot, and a student dashboard. Every idea in the six modules is
      practised on it, and the exemplar runs the whole loop, from zero to production.</p>
    <div class="toc-mini" aria-label="On this page">
      <a href="#arc">The course arc</a>
      <a href="#foundations">A0 &middot; Foundations</a>
      <a href="#modules">The six chapters</a>
      <a href="#exemplar">Portal exemplar</a>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section id="arc">
    <h2>The course arc</h2>
    <div class="prose">
      <p>Start with <strong>A0 &mdash; Foundations</strong>: the framework the rest of the course fills in. Its three
        pages are the whole method in miniature &mdash; the two layers, the four artifacts, and the loop &mdash; and
        they are built and readable now. <strong>A1</strong> makes the case for that framework. <strong>A2</strong> and
        <strong>A3</strong> teach decomposition into user stories and the roadmap that sequences them; <strong>A4</strong>
        and <strong>A5</strong> define the spec and the agent brief that turn a rung into running code;
        <strong>A6</strong> hardens every increment for reliability and correctness. The exemplar, <strong>A7</strong>,
        then runs the whole loop on Portal. The through line: a Claude agent is a fast, tireless implementer of
        <em>well-specified</em> thin slices, and the human is the source of decomposition, judgement, and acceptance.</p>
    </div>

    <figure class="fig" aria-labelledby="arcTitle">
      <h4 id="arcTitle" style="font-family:var(--sans);font-size:.8rem;letter-spacing:.16em;text-transform:uppercase;color:var(--cream-dim);margin:0 0 1rem">The framework, then the workflow, then the proof</h4>

