  <section id="foundations">
    <h2>A0 &middot; Foundations &mdash; what we are building</h2>
    <div class="prose">
      <p>Before the six chapters, the blueprint. This short foundations chapter lays out the framework the whole course
        runs on &mdash; its structure, its vocabulary, and its motion &mdash; in three pages that are the
        <strong>A0.2 &middot; What we are building</strong> module. They are built and readable now; read them first,
        and each later module fills in one part of the picture in depth.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="mods" style="margin-top:1.3rem">

      <a class="mod" href={PortalWeb.deep_link_base() <> "/course/agile-agent-workflow/what/two-layer-model"}>
        <div class="top"><span class="num">A0.2.1</span><span class="pill built">built</span></div>
        <p class="t">The two-layer model</p>
        <p class="o">The structure: a roadmap layer that plans delivery over a spec layer that defines and proves each
          rung &mdash; both on the framework-free core, the spec the single source of truth. Taught in depth by A3 and A4.</p>
      </a>

      <a class="mod" href={PortalWeb.deep_link_base() <> "/course/agile-agent-workflow/what/four-artifacts"}>
        <div class="top"><span class="num">A0.2.2</span><span class="pill built">built</span></div>
        <p class="t">The four artifacts</p>
        <p class="o">The vocabulary: a roadmap.md, a spec, the user stories, and the agent brief &mdash; four files, and
          the distinct question each answers. Each gets its own module: A3, A4, A2, and A5.</p>
      </a>

      <a class="mod" href={PortalWeb.deep_link_base() <> "/course/agile-agent-workflow/what/author-operator-loop"}>
        <div class="top"><span class="num">A0.2.3</span><span class="pill built">built</span></div>
        <p class="t">The Author/Operator loop</p>
        <p class="o">The motion: the human sharpens and accepts, the agent specifies and builds, the increment ships thin
          but robust, and feedback edits the spec. The loop A1 makes the case for, and A7 runs end to end.</p>
      </a>

    </div>

    <p class="note">These three pages are the <a href={PortalWeb.deep_link_base() <> "/course/agile-agent-workflow/what"}>A0.2 module hub</a>; the wider
      foundations chapter (<a href={PortalWeb.deep_link_base() <> "/course/agile-agent-workflow/what"}>A0 &middot; why, what, and who</a>) frames them.
      Read the framework first, then climb the ladder below.</p>
  </section>

